foia:ProcessedRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: After reviewing its database, BOP adjusted the number of requests pending as of the start of Fiscal Year 2009

EOIR reported 625 cases pending at the end of the fiscal year in the Fiscal Year 2008 Report. One case was processed but had not been counted as closed. Therefore, EOIR has adjusted the number of requests pending as of the start of Fiscal Year 2009 from 625 to 624.

After reviewing its database, JMD adjusted the number of requests pending as of the start of Fiscal Year 2009 to reflect two requests that had been processed in Fiscal Year 2008, but not reflected as closed in the system.
After reviewing its database, OJP adjusted the number of requests pending as of the start of Fiscal Year 2009.

After reviewing its database, OSG adjusted the number of requests pending as of the start of Fiscal Year 2009, determining that more Fiscal Year 2008 requests were added to the database after statistics were generated for the Fiscal Year 2008 Report.

foia:ProcessedResponseTimeSection.foia:FootnoteText: The following components' systems were unable to separate perfected and non-perfected processed and pending requests: Office of the AG, Office of the DAG, Office of the Assoc. AG, Antitrust, ATF, BOP, Civil, Civil Rights, DEA, NSD, OFDT, OIP, OIG, OIPL, OJP, OLP, OLA, Public Affairs, OSG, USPC.
JMD was unable to separate solely their perfected and non-perfected pending requests.

foia:SimpleResponseTimeIncrementsSection.foia:FootnoteText: ENRD does not have a formal multi-track processing system for "simple" versus "complex" requests. However, ENRD does issue interim responses in FOIA requests that are involved or complex and has reported these requests as "complex" and all others as "simple."

foia:PersonnelAndCostSection.foia:FootnoteText: Civil: The significant increase in processing costs from previous years is the result of the inclusion of the costs of "Equivalent Full-Time FOIA Employees" participating in administrative processing of requests. Past Reports included these individuals, but did not include their costs.
OJP: Information reflects FOIA staff only. Personnel in offices that search for responsive documents but are not FOIA staff were not captured.

foia:BacklogSection.foia:FootnoteText: OIP processes appeals for all DOJ components with the exception of USPC.

foia:ProcessedConsultationSection.foia:FootnoteText: DEA's number of consultations received from other agencies that were pending as of the start of Fiscal Year 2009 is slightly higher than the number reported in the Fiscal Year 2008 Report due to a DEA computer error.

In the Fiscal Year 2008 Report, EOUSA reported six pending consultations at the end of Fiscal Year 2008. This year's Report reflects five pending consultations at the start of Fiscal Year 2009 because one of EOUSA's requests was designated a consultation during Fiscal Year 2008, but upon further review it was determined that it was a referral. As a result, it was corrected in the database and processed as a referral instead of a consultation.
JMD inadvertently failed to include one consultation in its Fiscal Year 2008 Report.
OLC's system was unable to capture the number of consultations received from other agencies that were pending as of the start of Fiscal Year 2008.

foia:OldestPendingConsultationSection.foia:FootnoteText: In certain instances, the dates and number of days may not correspond because the request was tolled for a period of time. In addition, certain components' systems were unable to calculate working days, so calendar days are shown.
The Antitrust Division is waiting for the agency to send records to review in connection with the consultation process for its two oldest pending consultations.

foia:ProcessedRequestComparisonSection.foia:FootnoteText: In the Fiscal Year 2008 Report, JMD reported receiving 310 FOIA requests and processing 312 FOIA requests. However, after reviewing its database JMD adjusted these numbers because they had inadvertently included consultations.

foia:BackloggedRequestComparisonSection.foia:FootnoteText: The Criminal Division notes that due to system limitations, the number of backlogged requests as of the end of the fiscal year reported in the Fiscal Year 2008 Report was an estimate.
